wp-image-60095 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:1200px\" data-reactroot=\"\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:52.66666666666667%\"></span><img aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:0;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/7fd04f651e27098a62d323c5fd76269c/f2d49/1.png 300w,\n/static/7fd04f651e27098a62d323c5fd76269c/ff59c/1.png 600w,\n/static/7fd04f651e27098a62d323c5fd76269c/5ece7/1.png 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"/><img sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" srcSet=\"/static/7fd04f651e27098a62d323c5fd76269c/f2d49/1.png 300w,\n/static/7fd04f651e27098a62d323c5fd76269c/ff59c/1.png 600w,\n/static/7fd04f651e27098a62d323c5fd76269c/5ece7/1.png 1200w\" src=\"/static/7fd04f651e27098a62d323c5fd76269c/5ece7/1.png\" alt=\"Alamo Fireworks - The PM Group\" loading=\"eager\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"/></picture><noscript><picture><source srcset=\"/static/7fd04f651e27098a62d323c5fd76269c/f2d49/1.png 300w,\n/static/7fd04f651e27098a62d323c5fd76269c/ff59c/1.png 600w,\n/static/7fd04f651e27098a62d323c5fd76269c/5ece7/1.png 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /><img loading=\"eager\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" srcset=\"/static/7fd04f651e27098a62d323c5fd76269c/f2d49/1.png 300w,\n/static/7fd04f651e27098a62d323c5fd76269c/ff59c/1.png 600w,\n/static/7fd04f651e27098a62d323c5fd76269c/5ece7/1.png 1200w\" src=\"/static/7fd04f651e27098a62d323c5fd76269c/5ece7/1.png\" alt=\"Alamo Fireworks - The PM Group\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></span></figure></li></ul></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This summer’s firework season was a blast for <a href=\"https://www.alamofireworks.com/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\"undefined (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>Alamo Fireworks</strong></a>! This purveyor of all things lit was able to create new ways to continue serving their customers safely during COVID-19, all while having their most successful season yet.</p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:50px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Their summer campaign included audio streaming, a poppin’ segment on YOLO TX which gave viewers an inside look at what stands and megastores had to offer, a boomin’ social media push and digital campaign, new signage, product packaging, and price tags at all locations (853 individual tags to be exact!) Additionally, our efforts included billboards and OOH signage that helped navigate customers to find their nearest location. With creative brainpower from The PM Group, we were able to help Alamo Fireworks create and implement Alamo-To-Go curbside pickup, making it easy for buyers to safely stock up on crackin’ deals to make this past 4th of July lit AF. With over 175 stands and megastores open throughout the state of Texas, they reached more customers than ever before.</p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:50px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Our creative team kept the energy explosive with print design materials and touchpoints. From social distancing signage to staff t-shirts, to packaging designs for new fireworks, we enjoyed designing fun and cheeky material that really showcased the brand’s motto of creating happy memories.</p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:50px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter columns-3 is-cropped\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><span class=\"wp-image-60103 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper\"